{"title":"Streptococcus anginosus-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Infectología/Streptococcus anginosus-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Streptococcus\\Nanginosus","guid":"I34d9fzlMBlZJhLuTlN2wg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Contexto Clínico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Grupo: Antes conocido como Streptococcus milleri, incluye S. anginosus,\\NS. intermedius y S. constellatus (Clin Infect Dis 32:1511, 2001).","guid":"A2TEG0z3yX6vpYaqMgl54w","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Hábitat: Flora normal en boca y TGI, pero puede causar bacteriemia y\\Nformación de abscesos, lo que lo distingue de otros viridans streptococci.","guid":"N3k9N625-Zelw4gYqpsQvw","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Característica clave: Propensión a formar abscesos.","guid":"yUbHa84laYH8jUuoWZW-4w","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Identificación: Cocos Gram (+) con patrones de hemólisis variables\\N(alfa, beta o gamma) en agar sangre. Colonias con olor a caramelo.","guid":"JFd7gCpWXg2Jr_KfBNTWaA","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• Morfol: Cocos Gram (+) en cadenas.","guid":"HrUlpqYXx3FbHCEpaMtDCQ","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• Especies:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"• Streptococcus intermedius","guid":"XxRS5dsfuziY4GAJBSfkDw","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"• Streptococcus anginosus","guid":"olF-et0EkymzwfvmmIe8aA","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"• Streptococcus constellatus","guid":"Jvy0fcVilrJSe-ugJ82h0Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento Primario","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Sensibles a:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Beta-lactámicos: Penicilinas,\\Ncefalosporinas y carbapenémicos\\N(Antimicrob Agents Chemother 45:1511,\\N2001).","guid":"ZIlQ7GqzGQIOeNdMzIeRSg","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"• Dosis y elección dependen de: Sitio y\\Nseveridad de la infección.","guid":"SUrR46a2KbfmacA3Ttq95g","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"• Ej:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Absceso dental: Drenaje quirúrgico +\\NPen VK 500 mg VO c/6h antes de\\Ncomidas y al acostarse.","guid":"_gI8gYICE4CQuRe2JkuZ4g","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"• Absceso cerebral: Penicilina G, 18-24\\Nmillones de unidades dividido c/4-6h IV o\\NCeftriaxona 2 g IV c/12h.","guid":"ULlDZeCQQ9JibDvLTxRebA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"0","text":"Tratamientos\\NAlternativos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• Vancomicina: Activa y\\Nalternativa razonable.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"• Resistencia\\Nemergente:","guid":"o0BTfJzqFXgbkVIX-sqpEw","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• Fluoroquinolonas no son de\\Nprimera línea (J Antimicrob\\NChemother 2000;45:771).","guid":"GzM5ODMjB92BMdgcu79zJg","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"• Resistencia a macrólidos (J Med\\NMicrobiol 58:222, 2009).","guid":"okdPk0Xji6jcL61YrEUAuA","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"21","text":"• Muchos son resistentes a\\Naminoglucósidos.","guid":"QRTEvDeYlkNZzT53Y7pvLQ","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"21","text":"• Sulfonamidas\\Nno activas.","guid":"1cQwKsLt6DL0FA1bbYWnSA","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":25,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Infectología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Infectología","filename":"Streptococcus anginosus-2024","id":"map_1181","resolved_references":[]}